<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 3:38AM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Patchy dense fog has developed in sheltered areas of eastern New
York and western New England early this morning, with
visibilities reduced to a quarter to half mile in some spots.
Motorists should be alert for sudden changes in visibility. Leave
plenty of distance between vehicles. Slow down and allow for
extra time to reach your destination safely. The fog is expected
to dissipate by around 8 AM.</description>
